{"id":"311694215_The_complexity_of_proving_that_a_graph_is_Ramsey","abstract":"We say that a graph with n vertices is c-Ramsey if it does not contain either a clique or an independent set of size c log n. We define a CNF formula which expresses this property for a graph G. We show a superpolynomial lower bound on the length of resolution proofs that G is c-Ramsey, for every graph G. Our proof makes use of the fact that every c-Ramsey graph must contain a large subgraph with some properties typical for random graphs. © 2016 János Bolyai Mathematical Society and Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg","authors":["M. Lauria","P. Pudlák","V. Rödl","N. Thapen"],"meta":["February 2016Combinatorica 37(2):1-16","DOI:10.1007/s00493-015-3193-9"],"references":["3801353_Short_proofs_are_narrow-resolution_made_simple","2370656_Short_Proofs_are_Narrow_-_Resolution_made_Simple","2238359_Pseudorandom_Generators_in_Propositional_Proof_Complexity","303571623_Parameterized_complexity_of_DPLL_search_procedures","303568359_Parameterized_Bounded-Depth_Frege_Is_not_Optimal","284678693_Some_remarks_on_the_theory_of_graphs","283253872_Tautologies_from_pseudo-random_generators","265547591_Erdos_on_Graphs_His_Legacy_of_Unsolved_Problems","259764749_Clause-Learning_Algorithms_with_Many_Restarts_and_Bounded-Width_Resolution","232382145_Non-Ramsey_Graphs_Are_clogn-Universal","226603330_A_note_on_propositional_proof_complexity_of_some_Ramsey-type_statements","222549341_A_combinatorial_characterization_of_resolution_width","221590755_Examples_of_Hard_Tautologies_in_the_Propositional_Calculus","221557968_Ramsey's_Theorem_in_Bounded_Arithmetic","220546167_On_the_power_of_clause-learning_SAT_solvers_as_resolution_engines","220138255_Parameterized_Proof_Complexity_a_Complexity_Gap_for_Parameterized_Tree-like_Resolution","220138114_A_lower_bound_on_the_size_of_resolution_proofs_of_the_Ramsey_theorem","38383463_Lower_Bounds_to_the_Size_of_Constant-Depth_Propositional_Proofs"]}